
[1]steddiness

   STEADINESS, STEDDINESS, n.

   1. Firmness of standing or position; a state of being not tottering or
   easily moved or shaken. A man stands with steddiness; he walks with
   steddiness.

   2. Firmness of mind or purpose; constancy; resolution. We say, a man
   has steddiness of mind, steddiness in opinion, steddiness in the
   pursuit of objects.

   3. Consistent uniform conduct.

   Steddiness is a point of prudence as well as of courage.
